's name, it is often found as a male surname, presumably in a derogatory sense. The vocabulary word became <i>hussie</i>, with the meaning ‘disreputable woman’, in the 16th century; the surname, however, is not associated with this meaning.","Irish: shortened Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó hEodhusa</b> ‘descendant of <i>Eodhus</i>’. This was the name of a bardic family associated with the Maguires of Fermanagh, also Anglicized as   Oswell   or   Oswald  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Hosea","meanings":["English: variant of   Hussey  . Similarity with the Old Testament prophet's name Hosea (see 3 below) is accidental.","English: in Scotland, where the name is more common, it is sometimes a variant of   Hosie  , itself a form of   Hussey  , or else a variant of   Hossack  .","African (mainly Nigeria and Tanzania): from the Biblical personal name <i>Hosea</i>. In the Old Testament, Hosea was a prophet who married a prostitute in order to illustrate Israel's unfaithfulness to God."]},{"name":"Hosie","meanings":["Scottish (northeast Scotland): variant of Irish   Hussey  ."]},{"name":"Hassey","meanings":["Irish: variant of   Hussey  ."]},{"name":"Oswell","meanings":["English: variant of   Oswald  .","Irish (Ulster): adopted as an English equivalent of Gaelic <b>Ó hEodhusa</b> ‘descendant of <i>Eodhus</i>’ (see   Hussey  )."]},{"name":"Hosey","meanings":["English: variant of   Hussey  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Hussey was born about 1279, in Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 daughter with Geoffrey Blount."},"et":{"Abt 1279–":"umbes 1279–Surnud","1290–Male":"1290–Surnud","1320–1389":"1320–1389","1279–Female":"1279–Surnud","1279":"1279","1389":"1389","Abt 1320":"umbes 1320","1320":"1320","Abt 1279":"umbes 1279","1290":"1290",", , Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom":"Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1279–":"noin 1279–Kuollut","1290–Male":"1290–Kuollut","1320–1389":"1320–1389","1279–Female":"1279–Kuollut","1279":"1279","1389":"1389","Abt 1320":"noin